{{Infobox company | name = Semen Indonesia (Persero) Tbk | logo = File:Logo_Semen_Indonesia.JPG | type = [[Public company|Public]] | traded_as = {{IDX|SMGR}} | key_people = Hendi Prio Santoso (CE0), Sutiyoso (Commissioner) | industry = [[Building material]]s | products = [[Cement]]s, [[construction aggregates|aggregates]] | revenue = {{down}} [[Indonesian Rupiah|Rp]] 26.13&nbsp;trillion (2016) | assets = {{profit}} Rp 44.226&nbsp;trillion (2016) | net_income = {{profit}} [[Indonesian Rupiah|Rp]] 4.52&nbsp;trillion (2016) | num_employees = 6,592 (2015) | subsid = * [[Semen Gresik]] * [[Semen Tonasa]] * [[Semen Padang]] * [[Thang Long Cement]] * PT. Semen Indonesia Aceh * [[Semen Kupang]] | foundation = 1957 | location = [[Gresik]], [[Indonesia]] | homepage ={{url|semenindonesia.com}} }}
'''PT Semen Indonesia (Persero) Tbk''' or ''' Semen Indonesia''', formerly known as the '''Semen Gresik Group''',<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2013/01/07/semen-gresik-officially-becomes-semen-indonesia.html|title=Semen Gresik Officially becomes Semen Indonesia|date=January 7, 2013}}</ref> is an Indonesian [[building material]]s manufacturing company.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.indonesia-investments.com/doing-business/indonesian-companies/semen-indonesia/item194 |title=Indonesia-Investments.com:Semen Indonesia company profile |date=March 25, 2014}}</ref> . In shareholders' extraordinary meeting on December 20, 2012 the shareholders agreed to change name of PT Semen Gresik Tbk to PT Semen Indonesia Tbk to give a momentum for accelerating the company's growth in the future.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.antaranews.com/en/news/86314/semen-gresik-change-name-into-semen-indonesia |title=Semen Gresik change name into Semen Indonesia |date=December 20, 2012}}</ref>It has became the largest cement company in Southeast Asia with a production capacity of 53 million tons of cement per year after acquiring [[Holcim|PT Holcim Indonesia]] in November, 2018.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.thejakartapost.com/adv/2018/11/16/semen-indonesia-acquires-holcim-indonesia.html|title=Semen Indonesia acquires Holcim Indonesia|newspaper=The Jakarta Post|accessdate=16 November 2018}}</ref>
==Expansions== To secure supply and help lower its production costs, the company will set up a coal-trading firm in 2011 and further will seek possibility of coal mine acquisition. 30 percent of overall costs is coal consumption cost.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://english.kompas.com/read/2011/09/06/15110665/Semen.Gresik.Eyeing.To.Set.Up.Coal.Trading.Firm |title=Semen Gresik Eyeing To Set Up Coal Trading Firm |date=September 6, 2011}}</ref> PT. Semen Indonesia (Persero) Tbk acquired Thang Long Cement Vietnam officially January 2013. With the investment around Rp. 1,5 trillion, Semen Indonesia controls 70% of the Thang Long Cement shares.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://projectingindonesia.com/companies/pt-semen-indonesia-controls-70-shares-of-thang-long-cement-vietnam/ |title=PT. Semen Indonesia controls 70% shares of Thang Long Cement Vietnam |date=September 6, 2011}}</ref> The company also have announced its plan to invest US$200 million worth cement plant in [[Myanmar]] that will be built early in 2014 as part of its expansion into the Southeast Asian market.<ref name="GlobalCement">{{cite web |url =http://www.globalcement.com/news/item/1540-semen-indonesia-to-build-us$200m-plant-in-myanmar |title =Semen Indonesia to build US$200m plant in Myanmar |date =27 March 2013 |website =globalcement.com |publisher =Global Cement |accessdate =24 June 2013 }}</ref> In a bid to reduce logistics costs and bring it closer to its customers, PT Semen Indonesia is building a new packaging plant in Banjarmasin, South Kalimantan. The US$10.4m facility is due for completion by the end of 2013.<ref name="CemNet.com">{{cite web |url =http://www.cemnet.com/Corporate/story/153024/pt-semen-indonesia.html |title =PT Semen Indonesia - October 2013 |date =28 October 2013 |website =CemNet.com |publisher =International Cement Review |accessdate =31 October 2013 }}</ref>
==Incidents== In May 30, 2011 fire gutted 2 of PT [[Semen ]] IV machines in [[Bungoro]], [[South Sulawesi]] and halted the production for 10 days with financial losses of about Rp.45 billion ($5.3 million). The plant, owned by PT Semen Gresik Group.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2011/06/01/fire-halts-production-s-suluwesi-cement-factory.html |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2015-08-17 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110603100333/http://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2011/06/01/fire-halts-production-s-suluwesi-cement-factory.html |archivedate=2011-06-03 |df= }}</ref>
