{{Malay name|Zulkiflee|Wan Ariffin|note=on}} {{Infobox person | honorific_prefix = [[Malay titles|Yang Berbahagia Tan Sri]] | name = Wan Zulkiflee | image = | image_size = | caption = | birth_name = Wan Zulkiflee bin Wan Ariffin | birth_date = {{birth based on age as of date |57|2018|03|25}}<ref name=Bloomberg/> | birth_place = | death_date = | death_place = | residence = | nationality = Malaysian | education = [[University of Adelaide]] | occupation = Businessman | known for = | home_town = | salary = | networth = | title = CEO and president, [[Petronas]] | term = April 2015- | predecessor = Shamsul Azhar Abbas | successor = | boards = | spouse = | children = | parents = | relatives = | website = }} [[Malay titles|Tan Sri]] '''Wan Zulkiflee bin Wan Ariffin''' (born 1960/1961) is a Malaysian businessman, and the chief executive officer (CEO) and president of [[Petronas]], a state-owned Malaysian oil and gas producer, and a [[Fortune Global 500]] company.
==Early life== Wan Zulkiflee graduated with a bachelor's degree in Chemical Engineering from the [[University of Adelaide]], South Australia, and attended the six-week Advanced Management Program at [[Harvard Business School]] in 2004.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.utp.edu.my/The-University/Leadership/Pages/Pro-Chancellor.aspx|title=Leadership - Pro Chancellor|website=www.utp.edu.my|language=en-US|access-date=2018-11-01}}</ref>
==Career== He was appointed Pro Chancellor of Universiti Teknologi Petronas (UTP) in 2012.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.utp.edu.my/The-University/Leadership/SitePages/Pro%20Chancellor.aspx|title=Leadership - Pro Chancellor|website=www.utp.edu.my|language=en-US|access-date=2018-11-01}}</ref>
He has been CEO of Petronas since April 2015,<ref name=Bloomberg>{{cite web|title=Executive Profile* Wan Zulkiflee Bin Wan Ariffin|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/research/stocks/people/person.asp?personId=60014169&ticker=PETD:MK|website=Bloomberg|accessdate=31 July 2015}}</ref> taking over from Tan Sri Shamsul Azhar Abbas.<ref name=Star>{{cite news|title=Wan Zulkiflee Wan Ariffin appointed Petronas President/CEO|url=http://www.thestar.com.my/Business/Business-News/2015/02/09/Wan-Zulkiflee-Wan-Ariffin-appointed-Petronas-President-and-CEO/?style=biz|accessdate=31 July 2015|work=The Star|date=9 February 2015}}</ref> In June 2018, Attorney General of Sarawak requested that Petronas be relieved of its authority role in the oil and gas market in the Sarawak region.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thestar.com.my/business/business-news/2018/06/09/the-petronassarawak-oil-intrigue/|title=The Petronas-Sarawak oil intrigue - Business News {{!}} The Star Online|website=www.thestar.com.my|access-date=2018-10-29}}</ref> Zulkiflee has stated that oil and gas royalties and regulatory rights in the region were always under the authority of the Malaysian government, but consented to work toward a mutually acceptable working agreement nonetheless.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nst.com.my/business/2018/08/406563/petronas-awaits-federal-govt-decision-over-oil-royalty-issue-and-regulatory|title=Petronas awaits federal govt decision over oil royalty issue and regulatory rights in Sarawak|last=|first=|date=|website=|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=}}</ref>
In August 2018 Ahmad Nizam was appointed chairman of Petronas, however Zulkiflee maintained his position as CEO and president.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.theedgemarkets.com/article/ahmad-nizam-new-petronas-chairman-wan-zulkiflee-stay-president-ceo|title=Ahmad Nizam is new Petronas chairman, Wan Zulkiflee to stay on as president, CEO|date=2018-08-01|work=The Edge Markets|access-date=2018-10-29}}</ref>
